        <!-- Equipment Finance FAQs -->
        <section id="equipment-finance" class="faq-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Equipment Finance Questions</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What types of equipment can I finance through EVFBS?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We finance a comprehensive range of commercial equipment for established trades and contractors:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Heavy Machinery:</strong> Excavators, cranes, bulldozers, earthmoving equipment, concrete pumps</li>
                            <li><strong>Commercial Vehicles:</strong> Utes, trucks, vans, trailers, specialised service vehicles</li>
                            <li><strong>Trade Equipment:</strong> Welding machinery, HVAC equipment, electrical testing tools, workshop equipment</li>
                            <li><strong>Specialised Equipment:</strong> Mining equipment, agricultural machinery, medical equipment, IT infrastructure</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Finance amounts range from $20K to $500K+ with flexible terms from 1-7 years.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How quickly can I get equipment finance approval?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>For established commercial businesses with complete documentation, we typically provide:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Initial Assessment:</strong> Within 2-4 hours of application</li>
                            <li><strong>Approval Decision:</strong> 24-48 hours for straightforward applications</li>
                            <li><strong>Settlement:</strong> 5-10 business days depending on equipment verification</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Urgent equipment acquisitions can often be expedited with our priority service for time-sensitive projects.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What are the typical interest rates for equipment finance?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Commercial equipment finance rates vary based on several factors:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Typical Range:</strong> 6% to 15% per annum</li>
                            <li><strong>Prime Commercial:</strong> 6-9% for strong financials and new equipment</li>
                            <li><strong>Standard Commercial:</strong> 9-12% for established businesses</li>
                            <li><strong>Specialist Finance:</strong> 12-15% for unique situations or older equipment</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Rates depend on business financial strength, equipment type, loan term, and security offered. We negotiate competitive rates through our specialist lender network.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Should I choose equipment loan, lease, or hire purchase?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Each option offers different benefits for commercial businesses:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Equipment Loan:</strong> Immediate ownership, full depreciation benefits, equipment as security</li>
                            <li><strong>Equipment Lease:</strong> Lower payments, 100% tax deductible, upgrade options, operational expense</li>
                            <li><strong>Hire Purchase:</strong> Fixed payments, balloon options, ownership at completion, GST benefits</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Our specialists will recommend the optimal structure based on your cash flow, tax position, and business objectives.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Can I finance used or second-hand equipment?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes, we regularly finance quality used equipment with specific considerations:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Age Limits:</strong> Typically equipment under 10 years old (varies by type)</li>
                            <li><strong>Condition Assessment:</strong> Professional evaluation may be required</li>
                            <li><strong>Finance Terms:</strong> Usually shorter terms (2-5 years) for used equipment</li>
                            <li><strong>Higher Deposit:</strong> May require 10-20% deposit depending on age and condition</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Quality used equipment from reputable dealers often qualifies for competitive rates.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Commercial Property Finance FAQs -->
        <section id="commercial-property" class="faq-section alt-bg">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Commercial Property Finance Questions</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What commercial properties can I finance for my business?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We specialise in commercial property finance for:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Business Premises:</strong> Warehouses, workshops, offices, retail spaces</li>
                            <li><strong>Industrial Properties:</strong> Manufacturing facilities, storage, distribution centres</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment Properties:</strong> Commercial real estate for rental income</li>
                            <li><strong>Development Projects:</strong> Commercial development and construction finance</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Finance amounts from $100K to $5M+ with terms from 5-30 years depending on property type and use.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What deposit is required for commercial property finance?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Deposit requirements vary by property type and use:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Owner-Occupier:</strong> 10-20% for established businesses purchasing premises</li>
                            <li><strong>Investment Property:</strong> 20-30% for commercial investment purchases</li>
                            <li><strong>Development Finance:</strong> 20-40% depending on project type and experience</li>
                            <li><strong>Specialised Properties:</strong> 30-50% for unique or limited-use properties</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Existing business equity and equipment can sometimes be used as additional security to reduce cash deposit requirements.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How long does commercial property finance approval take?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Commercial property approval timeframes typically include:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Pre-Approval:</strong> 2-5 business days with complete documentation</li>
                            <li><strong>Formal Approval:</strong> 10-15 business days after property valuation</li>
                            <li><strong>Settlement:</strong> 30-45 days from contract exchange</li>
                            <li><strong>Complex Deals:</strong> 6-8 weeks for development or unique properties</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Having pre-approval strengthens your position when negotiating property purchases.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Can I use commercial property equity for business growth?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes, commercial property equity can be leveraged for business expansion:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Equipment Finance:</strong> Property equity as additional security for lower rates</li>
                            <li><strong>Working Capital:</strong> Business line of credit secured by property</li>
                            <li><strong>Business Expansion:</strong> Funding for new locations or business diversification</li>
                            <li><strong>Refinancing:</strong> Access equity while securing better terms</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>We structure solutions to optimise tax benefits and maintain healthy debt service ratios.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Working Capital FAQs -->
        <section id="working-capital" class="faq-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Working Capital & Cash Flow Questions</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What working capital solutions are available for commercial trades?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We offer flexible working capital solutions tailored to commercial trades:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Business Line of Credit:</strong> $50K-$500K revolving credit for operational flexibility</li>
                            <li><strong>Invoice Factoring:</strong> Convert invoices to immediate cash (80-95% advance)</li>
                            <li><strong>Seasonal Funding:</strong> Support for peak demand periods and project cycles</li>
                            <li><strong>Bridging Finance:</strong> Short-term funding for payment delays or opportunities</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Solutions are structured to match your business cash flow patterns and industry cycles.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How does a business line of credit work?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>A business line of credit provides flexible access to working capital:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Credit Limit:</strong> Approved limit (e.g., $100K) that you can draw against as needed</li>
                            <li><strong>Interest Charges:</strong> Pay interest only on amounts drawn, not the full limit</li>
                            <li><strong>Repayment:</strong> Flexible repayments with ability to redraw</li>
                            <li><strong>Security:</strong> Can be secured by property, equipment, or business assets</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Ideal for managing cash flow gaps, taking advantage of supplier discounts, or funding growth opportunities.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What are the qualification criteria for working capital finance?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Working capital qualification typically requires:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Business Operation:</strong> Minimum 12 months trading history</li>
                            <li><strong>Financial Performance:</strong> Positive cash flow and sustainable business model</li>
                            <li><strong>Credit History:</strong> Acceptable business and director credit profiles</li>
                            <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Current financial statements and business plans</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Established businesses with consistent performance typically qualify for competitive rates and terms.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Invoice Financing FAQs -->
        <section id="invoice-financing" class="faq-section alt-bg">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Invoice Financing Questions</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How does invoice financing work for commercial trades?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Invoice financing provides immediate cash from unpaid commercial invoices:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Initial Advance:</strong> Receive 80-95% of invoice value within 24 hours</li>
                            <li><strong>Client Payment:</strong> Your clients pay invoices normally (often confidential)</li>
                            <li><strong>Final Payment:</strong> Receive balance less fees when client pays</li>
                            <li><strong>Non-Recourse Options:</strong> Protection against client default available</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Particularly effective for businesses with 30-90 day payment terms from commercial clients.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What types of invoices qualify for financing?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>We finance invoices from creditworthy commercial clients:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>B2B Invoices:</strong> Business-to-business transactions with commercial clients</li>
                            <li><strong>Government Work:</strong> Local, state, and federal government contracts</li>
                            <li><strong>Large Corporates:</strong> ASX-listed companies and major corporations</li>
                            <li><strong>Established SMEs:</strong> Medium-sized businesses with good payment history</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Consumer invoices and residential work generally don't qualify for commercial invoice financing.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What are the costs associated with invoice financing?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Invoice financing costs typically include:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Factoring Fee:</strong> 1.5-4% of invoice value depending on client quality</li>
                            <li><strong>Interest Charges:</strong> Monthly interest on advances (1-3% per month)</li>
                            <li><strong>Setup Fees:</strong> $500-$2000 for initial due diligence and setup</li>
                            <li><strong>Management Fees:</strong> Ongoing account management (often included)</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Total cost typically ranges from 15-25% annually, often justified by improved cash flow and growth opportunities.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Application Process FAQs -->
        <section id="application-process" class="faq-section">
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Application Process Questions</h2>
                
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What documents do I need for a commercial finance application?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Required documentation varies by finance type but typically includes:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Financial Statements:</strong> 2 years business financials (profit & loss, balance sheet)</li>
                            <li><strong>BAS Statements:</strong> Recent quarterly BAS lodgements</li>
                            <li><strong>Bank Statements:</strong> 6 months business and personal statements</li>
                            <li><strong>Equipment Documentation:</strong> Quotes, invoices, or valuations</li>
                            <li><strong>Business Registration:</strong> ABN, ACN, business licences</li>
                            <li><strong>Director Identification:</strong> Licence, passport, or proof of identity</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>We provide a comprehensive checklist during initial consultation to streamline the process.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>Do you work with businesses that have imperfect credit history?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Yes, we specialise in finding solutions for businesses with various credit situations:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Credit Impairments:</strong> Defaults, late payments, or judgements</li>
                            <li><strong>Previous Bankruptcies:</strong> Discharged bankruptcies with current strong performance</li>
                            <li><strong>New Business:</strong> Limited credit history but strong business fundamentals</li>
                            <li><strong>Industry Challenges:</strong> Businesses affected by economic conditions</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Our extensive lender network includes specialists who focus on business performance and security rather than just credit scores.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>How much can I borrow for my business?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Borrowing capacity depends on multiple factors:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Business Cash Flow:</strong> Ability to service debt comfortably</li>
                            <li><strong>Security Available:</strong> Property, equipment, or business assets</li>
                            <li><strong>Business Strength:</strong> Financial performance and stability</li>
                            <li><strong>Industry Factors:</strong> Sector-specific lending criteria</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>General guidelines: Equipment finance $20K-$500K+, Property finance $100K-$5M+, Working capital $50K-$1M+. We provide detailed capacity assessments during consultation.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="faq-item">
                    <h3>What security is required for commercial finance?</h3>
                    <div class="faq-answer">
                        <p>Security requirements vary by loan type and amount:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Equipment Finance:</strong> Equipment itself plus business guarantees</li>
                            <li><strong>Property Finance:</strong> Property mortgage plus business guarantees</li>
                            <li><strong>Working Capital:</strong> Business assets, property, or equipment</li>
                            <li><strong>Unsecured Options:</strong> Limited amounts based on strong financials</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>Personal guarantees from directors are standard, but personal property security depends on loan size and risk assessment.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

